title: Shark attack sparks calls for cull, new hate speech and gun laws passed | 7NEWS
description: Multiple shark attacks across New South Wales have resulted in dozens of beach closures, with a surfer escaping with minor injuries on the mid-north coast while two victims in Sydney remain critically injured. The state government has increased drumline and drone surveillance but ruled out shark culls despite mounting pressure. Federal parliament has passed new hate speech and gun laws after a marathon 13-hour Senate sitting, allowing authorities to ban groups like Hizb ut-Tahrir and requiring ASIO background checks on gun licence applicants and their family members. title: Four shark attacks in 48 hours spark calls for cull | 7NEWS
description: New South Wales beaches face closures after four shark attacks occur within 48 hours. A surfer on the mid-north coast sustained minor injuries and board damage, while in Sydney, 27-year-old Andre de Reuter and 12-year-old Nico Antic remain critically injured, with the boy not expected to survive. Authorities have deployed additional drumlines and drone surveillance as public pressure grows for a shark cull, which the state government has rejected. title: Federal government passes hate speech and gun laws | 7NEWS
description: The Australian federal government has passed new hate speech and gun laws following a marathon Senate sitting that extended past 11pm. The hate speech legislation enables the banning of groups like Hizb ut-Tahrir and the National Socialist Network, while the gun laws introduce ASIO background checks on weapons licence applicants and their family members, along with a national gun buyback scheme facing resistance from Queensland, Northern Territory and Tasmania.
